REMARK 280 CRYSTALLIZATION CONDITIONS: A RACEMIC MIXTURE OF L-AUREOCIN A53      
REMARK 280  AND D-AUREOCIN A53 AT 40 MG/ML CONCENTRATION WAS MIXED 1:1 WITH     
REMARK 280  0.2 M AMMONIUM ACETATE, 0.2 M SODIUM CITRATE AND 29% PEG 4000 V/    
REMARK 280  V PRECIPITANT CONDITION, PH 5.6 IN A 1 MICROLITRE SITTING DROP.     
REMARK 280  THE CRYSTAL WAS SOAKED WITH SN-GLYCEROL-3-PHOSPHATE (334 MM IN      
REMARK 280  THE PRECIPITANT SOLUTION) AT 1:1 V/V FOR 24 HOURS (50               
REMARK 280  EQUIVALENTS). CRYSTALS WERE SUBMERGED IN 20% PEG 400 IN THE         
REMARK 280  PRECIPITANT SOLUTION AS CRYOPROTECTANT AND FLASH FROZEN IN          
REMARK 280  LIQUID NITROGEN DURING HARVESTING., VAPOR DIFFUSION, SITTING        
REMARK 280  DROP, TEMPERATURE 292K                                              
